Climate impacts on crop yields will lead to an additional 20 million children being malnourished by 2050. This would be catastrophic in Africa.During services, a few minutes could be set aside to educate the masses on how global warming is causing climate change. Never in the history of the earth has carbon dioxide levels risen so fast. The world over, climate change is being fuelled by human activities, such as excessive emissions of greenhouse gases since the start of the industrial revolution.
According to the World Food Program, extreme weather events like floods, droughts, forest fires, and tropical cyclones that are caused by climate change are threatening food security for millions of people.



