While governments dither on their responses, the church can lead the way and inspire millions of followers to take action. After all, the Bible clearly states that we are the guardians of the world.
For a start, the church could educate the masses on how global warming is causing climate change, and how our children will have it rough if nothing is done. During services, a few minutes could be set aside for this purpose.
Once masses understand this, they could easily influence state policies. What happens on earth in 100 years will depend on the choices we make to-day. Detectives will review footage capturing events of September 21 at around 10am outside the KRA offices. A spot check by the Nation found patients lying helpless in beds with relatives preferring to transfer them to private hospitals The talks aim to reach consensus before referendum signatures are handed to IEBC.